						<summary>

						<p>In the same place.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Paridhāvi = 1492 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is damaged and seems to be incomplete.</p>						

						<p>It records an endowment of a dancing girl named Nāyapeṟṟāḷ (?) to the temple of Tirumuttīchchuram-uḍaiya-nāyaṉār of Muduśōṟkuḍi-nāḍu, perhaps by Kaṉakarāyarpiḷḷai Daṉamōda and the gift was accepted by the <hi rend="italic">adikāri</hi> Śellapperumāḷ. The signatory was the temple accountant named Koḍumbaināyakavēḷār Śīmāṉppiḷḷai Maṉṟamuḍaiyāṉ.</p>						

						</summary>
